<section id="overview" class="container">
    <h1 class="sectionHeader">Download</h1>

    <p class="introBlock">
        You can go about install Core Framework either using Git or Composer. Though we strongly recommend that you use
        Composer to install Core Framework. With composer you can use the following command to download Core Framework -
    </p>
    <pre class="prettyprint lang-shell">composer create-project core-framework&#47;core-framework &#47;var&#47;www&#47;CoreFramework "v2.0.0-beta"</pre>
    <p class="para"><strong>OR</strong> with Git you can use -</p>
    <pre class="prettyprint lang-shell">git clone https:&#47;&#47;github.com&#47;core-framework&#47;core-framework.git path&#47;to&#47;directory</pre>
    <p class="para">and then checkout a specific branch and then use <code class="prettyprint lang-bash">composer
            install</code> to download dependencies.</p>

    <p class="well well-small">
        <strong>NOTE:</strong> For a more detail set of instructions please checkout the <a href="/get_started">Get
            Started</a> section.
    </p>
</section>